filewrite - writes text into a file

Description:
The 'filewrite' command writes the provided text into the specified file. If the file already exists, it must be a text file. A newline is added at the end of the written text. If no file name or text is provided, or if an error occurs during writing, an error message is shown.

Usage:
filewrite <file_name> <text>

Examples:
filewrite notes.txt "Hello World"
filewrite # Error: Invalid name or text provided.
filewrite binary.dat "Test" # Error: Existing file 'binary.dat' is not a text file.
